<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Lorillard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-19"><hi rend="italic">December 19,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that a general
                            treaty of arbitration between Denmark and Italy was signed on the 14th
                            instant at Rome.</p>
                        <p>While the text of the treaty has not yet been made public, I am in a
                            position to state that by its terms all differences which may occur
                            between the two countries are to be referred to the Permanent Court of.
                            Arbitration at The Hague for final settlement.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">George L.
                            Lorillard.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>